import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    ax = sns.barplot(x='count', y='origin', data=data)
    ax.set_xlabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_ylabel('Airport')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What are the top 10 busiest airports in terms of number of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'])
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values('count', ascending=False).head(20)
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x='origin', y='destination', size='count', data=data, sizes=(50, 500), alpha=0.7)
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin')
    ax.set_ylabel('Destination')
    ax.set_title('What are the most popular routes in terms of number of flights?', wrap=True)
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).mean().reset_index()
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x='origin', y='destination', size='count', data=data, sizes=(50, 500), legend=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Destination Airport')
    ax.set_title('What is the average number of flights between different airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'], errors='coerce')
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    if len(data) > 0:
        ax = sns.scatterplot(x='distance', y='count', data=data)
        ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
        ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
        ax.xaxis.label.set_rotation(45)
        if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
            ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the correlation between distance and number of flights between different airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
